<div id="review_147834774" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/147834774" />
    <a title="Igomigo1" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4971141-igomigo1"><img alt="Igomigo1" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/147834774?book_show_action=true">Feb 12, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Igomigo1" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Igomigo1" href="/user/show/4971141-igomigo1">Igomigo1</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer147834774&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer147834774" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12707408648493845856">This book is great. The title of the book seems to be misleading, but don&apos;t let that fool you. This book represents hardships, life, and a kid who is so cute! The book at first, has chapters dedicated to introducing each characters such as Ullysses, Homer, Bess and Mary, Mr.Grogan, etc.<br/>The book is set at Ithaca, California and starts out with Ullysses, the cute kid, talking to a hobo. Starts out very funny. Then the story reveals that the father died at war I think, and their brother Marcus was </span>
  <span id="freeText12707408648493845856" style="display:none">This book is great. The title of the book seems to be misleading, but don't let that fool you. This book represents hardships, life, and a kid who is so cute! The book at first, has chapters dedicated to introducing each characters such as Ullysses, Homer, Bess and Mary, Mr.Grogan, etc.<br />The book is set at Ithaca, California and starts out with Ullysses, the cute kid, talking to a hobo. Starts out very funny. Then the story reveals that the father died at war I think, and their brother Marcus was at war too. (Marcus' friend came to Ullysses' house to send a telegram that Marcus was dead)<br />The story is very descriptive and goes through every person's viewpoint of the world.<br /><br />The story is mostly based on Ullysses viewpoint, and shows what happens to him. He seems to have high hopes of Marcus coming home. You sometimes feel sad for him because of his lack of knowledge of what is happening around him, and a lot of people hushes around him so they won't disturb his childhood. But eventually he finds out about life, and its hardship.<br /><br />What I Loved About The Book:<br />Good story, realistic characters, real feelings and not something that would come out of a corny drama script, very cute talking kid named Ullysses, good brother named Homer, parents are not very shown.<br /><br />What I Hated About The Book:<br />Homer buying day-old pies and eating them with his boss or manager.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12707408648493845856" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


